ng_public_at":"2017-07-12T14:35:43.811Z","comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"I reported this bug privately to Mercurial and they produced an out of band release to fix the bug here:\n\nhttps://www.mercurial-scm.org/wiki/WhatsNew#Mercurial_4.1.3_.282017-4-18.29\n\nI produced a very detailed proof of concept with a Metasploit exploit module, which can be seen publicly here:\n\nhttps://github.com/rapid7/metasploit-framework/pull/8263\n\nThe TLDR is that many services which host Mercurial servers often write their own hg-ssh wrapper or heavily customize the hg-ssh wrapper.  If the customized wrapped does not explicitly validate user input to the repo attribute, an attacker can supply a string of \"--debugger\", which causes the internal hg binary to drop to a Pdb shell, which allows arbitrary Python code execution.\n\nI'm submitting to this program because I believe source code management software like git and mercurial is considered critical infrastructure for the Internet.","vulnerability_information_html":"\u003cp\u003eI reported this bug privately to Mercurial and they produced an out of band release to fix the bug here:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://www.mercurial-scm.org/wiki/WhatsNew#Mercurial_4.1.3_.282017-4-18.29\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mercurial-scm.org%2Fwiki%2FWhatsNew%23Mercurial_4.1.3_.282017-4-18.29\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://www.mercurial-scm.org/wiki/WhatsNew#Mercurial_4.1.3_.282017-4-18.29\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI produced a very detailed proof of concept with a Metasploit exploit module, which can be seen publicly here:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca title=\"https://github.com/rapid7/metasploit-framework/pull/8263\" href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Frapid7%2Fmetasploit-framework%2Fpull%2F8263\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003ehttps://github.com/rapid7/metasploit-framework/pull/8263\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe TLDR is that many services which host Mercurial servers often write their own hg-ssh wrapper or heavily customize the hg-ssh wrapper.  If the customized wrapped does not explicitly validate user input to the repo attribute, an attacker can supply a string of \u0026quot;--debugger\u0026quot;, which causes the internal hg binary to drop to a Pdb shell, which allows arbitrary Python code execution.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eI\u0026#39;m submitting to this program because I believe source code management software like git and mercurial is considered critical infrastructure for the Internet.\u003c/p\u003e\n","bounty_amount":"500.0","formatted_bounty":"$500","weakness":{"id":70,"name":"Code Injection"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[],"allow_singular_disclosure_at":"2017-08-11T14:35:43.850Z","allow_singular_disclosure_after":-106755911.78659895,"singular_disclosure_allowed":true,"vote_count":3,"voters":["eveeez","geeknik","0xradi"],"severity":{"rating":"high","author_type":"User"},"structured_scope":null,"abilities":{"assignable_team_members":[],"assignable_team_member_groups":[]},"can_edit_custom_fields_attributes":false,"activities":[{"id":1827645,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::CveIdAdded","message":"","markdown_message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2017-07-12T09:35:37.306Z","updated_at":"2017-07-12T09:35:37.306Z","cve_ids":["CVE-2017-9462"],"actor":{"username":"arice","cleared":false,"url":"/arice","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/020/83152cb2d070f3f6a63c1b61bae47257722b5ad2_original.jpeg/eb31823a4cc9f6b6bb4db930ffdf512533928a68a4255fb50a83180281a60da5"},"h